---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
const lang = 'en';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang={lang}>
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Agro2Code Blog</h1>
			<p>
				This site is the editorial space connected to the Agro2Code portfolio. It is where
				long-form articles, experiments, technical notes, and discussions live after a reader
				chooses to open a topic from the main portfolio.
			</p>
			<p>
				The current focus is a publishing flow that is fast, predictable, and easy to evolve:
				Markdown or MDX content, stable URLs, GitHub Pages deployment, and an Obsidian-first
				authoring workflow.
			</p>
			<p>Core principles for this project:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Publish PT-BR content first, with EN support preserved</li>
				<li>Keep canonical URLs stable for portfolio integration</li>
				<li>Validate content contracts before every release</li>
				<li>Grow the project through TDD and small, reversible changes</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Use the blog navigation to browse published posts. The editorial and architecture
				decisions are documented in the repository for implementation continuity.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
